			<h3 ><a href="#p25074"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=25074#p25074"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1450">Nokei</a></strong> &raquo; Feb 15th, '04, 03:08 </p>

			

			<div class="content">Back to Ad's original quest - here is a recent example:
<br />
<br />I normally duo in tactics with a druid (the infamous Arm/Supp camp).  We decided to invite a cleric along to speed the killing a little.  My pet - a death knight or armsman - is tanking away the first couple mobs just fine.  All of a sudden, a mob breaks off and starts moving towards me.  I still have a pet, so what could be the matter?  Cleric casted her hammer pet.
<br />
<br />Pet Tank + Druid + Me + Cleric + Hammer = 5 and no go.
<br />
<br />I believe, but am not sure - that a summoned pet puts both the pet and the caster on the hate list (regardless if the caster does anything or not independently).  Had the same thing happen in HoH when a shammy in our trio summoned Gebaner.</div>

