		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p25104">Sigh</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=25104#p25104"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=758">Lone_War</a></strong> &raquo; Feb 15th, '04, 13:27 </p>

			

			<div class="content">No, there is NO limit on the number of things on a mobs agro list which says it will stop pounding on pets and start pounding on players.
<br />
<br />My standard group is ENC (DC or charmed pet), DRU (DC pet), Mage (Air pet), CLR (Hammer pet), WIZ (Sword pet), all except me nuking, cleric healing, and me pulling with a tash and early slow.
<br />
<br />And the mage pet tanks it just fine.
<br />
<br />So there is no 4 mob rule or whatever. Not sure why the above posters get agro, but its not because of a mythical 4 mob limit.</div>

			<div id="sig25104" class="signature">Sage Sassnik Dreameweaver, Tunare (Krieger)
<br />Not Maxed In:
<br />Blacksmithing 221
<br />Tailoring 220</div>

