		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p28424"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=28424#p28424"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=842">Fadnae</a></strong> &raquo; Mar 4th, '04, 13:28 </p>

			

			<div class="content">From experience if a pet does not start with agro and there are 5 or more on the mob's hate list, the pet will NEVER gain agro (while 5 or more are on the hate list).  This goes from the newbie snakes to the 1200+ hitters in GoD.  The reasoning behind it is simple.  EQ is coded so that as soon as more than 4 are on a mob's hate list it will not attack a pet.  The exception to this is if root is applied.  Then proximity agro takes over.  
<br />
<br />If a pet starts with agro and 5 or more get onto the mob's hatelist, the mob will agro the player with the highest agro.  The rule of 4 is in effect and does apply for pets (charmed or summoned).</div>

			<div id="sig28424" class="signature"><img src="http://www.geocities.com/fadnae/fadsignature.jpg" alt="Image" />
<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=398646" class="postlink">Fadnae Vancoia</a>
<br />The wicked...errr..."Good" Witch with the <a href="http://www.stormspirits.com" class="postlink">Storm Spirits</a>
<br /><span style="font-size: 75%; line-height: 116%;">E70.540/I h+ 7.1khp 8.7km ft17 G!&lt;3 e+++++ o+ T+++++ L++ H++(---)@ f+ g b-- c+++ t+++ FP!G++O E+ S! FE++ !TR !GT</span></div>

		</div>

		
