	<div id="p32093" class="post bg2">
		<div class="inner"><span class="corners-top"><span></span></span>

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p32093"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=32093#p32093"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=184">desseray</a></strong> &raquo; Mar 23rd, '04, 15:03 </p>

			

			<div class="content">The 4 person agro rule ONLY applies to CHARMED PETS. If you have a summoned pet, it does not matter how many people are on the agro list. The only things that matter in that situation are:
<br />
<br />Are any PCs in melee range of the mob? If so, pet wont hold agro.
<br />
<br />and 2
<br />
<br />Does the pet have enough agro generated to hold it? If not, just like a warrior, you will out taunt it.</div>

			<div id="sig32093" class="signature">Desseray Lokheart &lt;Frayed Knot&gt;
<br />75 - The Rathe</div>

		</div>

		
