			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=32833#p32833"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1450">Nokei</a></strong> &raquo; Mar 27th, '04, 00:46 </p>

			

			<div class="content">Tried something for the hell of it this week.  Pet Tanking Vindi.
<br />
<br />First attempt:
<br />
<br />2 Chanters with buffed DC pets
<br />Ranger pulled without appropriate warning/instruction, Vindi ping-pongs when second pet engages (4 limit hate list rule)
<br />Result:  Wipe
<br />
<br />Second attempt:
<br />The 4 limit rule now explained to raid, and the gimpness of 10Kish pets trying to tank vindi without heals, I convince the raid to take another approach:
<br />
<br />2 Chanters Beckon 2 PoZs
<br />I pet-pull vindi on the bridge
<br />Both pets engage, pet 2 starts healing pet 1 (woohoo)
<br />Vindi 90 pct - Guardians come to his aid out of no where (we had killed them earlier on first attempt)
<br />I tash and pull 1 guardian off, root it.
<br />Ranger calls "off tank"
<br />I say "NOOOO"
<br />Raid engages guardian, Vindi (must be linked to hate list cause he was a good distance away) ping-pongs.
<br />
<br />Result:  Wipe
<br />
<br />We learned from the first attempt and had a rezzer camped at least.
<br />
<br />Was great fun nonetheless.
